  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Offsets are activities that reduce emissions of CO2 or work to decrease the amount of CO2 in the atmosphere. CO2 emission is known as one of the main causes of climate change.   Aid for Social Protection Foundation Vietnam (AFV) is starting a unique carbon offset project - planting trees in schools, communities and highland areas where huge areas of sloping land are vacant, after people have stopped shifting cultivation.</narrative>
